SIMPLE: profound
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Profound
<hw>Pro*found"</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>profond</ets>, L.
<ets>profundus</ets>; pro before, forward + <ets>fundus</ets> the
bottom. See <er>Found</er> to establish, <er>Bottom</er> lowest
part.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Descending far below the surface; opening
or reaching to a great depth; deep.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A gulf
<xex>profound</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Intellectually deep; entering far into subjects;
reaching to the bottom of a matter, or of a branch of learning;
thorough; <as>as, a <ex>profound</ex> investigation or treatise; a
<ex>profound</ex> scholar; <ex>profound</ex> wisdom.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Characterized by intensity; deeply felt; pervading;
overmastering; far-reaching; strongly impressed; <as>as, a
<ex>profound</ex> sleep</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Profound</xex>
sciatica.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Of the <qex>profound</qex> corruption of this class there can be
no doubt.</q> <rj><qau>Milman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Bending low, exhibiting or expressing deep humility;
lowly; submissive; <as>as, a <ex>profound</ex> bow</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What humble gestures! What <qex>profound</qex> reverence!</q>
<rj><qau>Duppa.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Profound</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Profound
<hw>Pro*found"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
deep; the sea; the ocean.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God in the fathomless <qex>profound</qex>⟦br⟧
Hath all this choice commanders drowned.</q>
<rj><qau>Sandys.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An abyss.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Profound</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Profound
<hw>Pro*found"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To cause to sink deeply; to
cause to dive or penetrate far down.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Profound</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Profound
<hw>Pro*found"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To dive deeply; to
penetrate.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Profoundly</ent>⟦br⟧
